headline: This 'Shark Tank' Startup Did $95 Million In Sales Last Year. Its Founders Say They Bootstrapped Their Success
summary: Twin sisters Taylor Capuano and Casey Sarai found themselves at a crossroads in their careers in 2022. Instead of taking a more traditional route, the women elected to start their own company, Cakes Body, which now does millions in sales each year. Three years ago, Capuano was a marketing manager at the clothing brand Life Is Good and had just welcomed her first child.
